title: Truck hits car in Pasco, sending 2 to hospital
text:
October 6, 2015 Truck hits car in Pasco, sending 2 to hospital A semi-truck and tractor hit a passenger car Tuesday morning after taking the exit ramp off Highway 12 toward Lewis Street in Pasco. The driver may have failed to stop at the stop sign, said investigators. Two people in the car were hurt and taken to a hospital to be checked. Bob Brawdy Tri-City Herald i Order Reprint of this Story 
A semi-truck and tractor hit a passenger car Tuesday morning after taking the exit ramp off Highway 12 toward Lewis Street in Pasco. 
The driver may have failed to stop at the stop sign, said investigators. Two people in the car were hurt and taken to a hospital to be checked. The injuries were not life threatening, said officials at the scene. Related content
